1. Language key validation on save
Any language key in content, title, body, question, answer is now validated against the active Language table. Trying to save {"zz": "..."} returns:


{ "error": "Invalid language codes: ['zz']. Active languages: ['en', 'ml']" }
2. ?lang= filter on all GET endpoints
Pass ?lang=ml to any admin CMS GET and instead of raw JSON you get:


{
  "block_key": "hero_headline",
  "content": "കർഷക ഉൽപാദക സംഘടനകളെ...",
  "available_languages": ["en", "ml"],
  "is_active": true
}
3. How to add a new language (e.g. Tamil)

Admin adds Tamil via POST /api/admin/languages/ → { "code": "ta", "name": "Tamil", ... }
Now "ta" is a valid key — CMS validation accepts it
Admin PATCHes any block with { "content": { "en": "...", "ml": "...", "ta": "..." } }
Frontend sends X-Language: ta → gets Tamil text back





